FBIS4-48568 "drafr099_a_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-099 Daily Report 22 May 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Take Control of Airport Take Control of Airport EA2205144294 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in French to Rwanda 1030 GMT 22 May 94 EA2205144294 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura French BFN [Excerpt] The Rwandan Patriotic Army [RPA] continues to score points. The international airport at Kanombe near Kigali and the Kanombe camp of Colonel (Mayuya) are under the total control of the RPA, the armed wing of the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF], as of this morning. Under siege for several days, the Col. (Mayuya) camp finally fell today to the combatants of the RPA. Many soldiers left their [word indistinct] behind. Enormous quantities of arms were seized. Government troops who fled the onslaught of the Inkotanyi [rebels] did not have time to take their arms and ammunition. [passage omitted]
